Package com.amitinside.featureflags

Provides API for managing all Feature instances

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Configurable
    A class implements the Configurable interface to indicate that the instance is configurable through OSGi Configuration Admin and hence is a participant in this feature flags implementation.
    FeatureManager
    The FeatureManager service is the applications access point to the feature flags functionality.
    Strategizable
    A class implements the Strategizable interface to indicate that the instances of the class can be used to provide strategic information for its enablement.
    StrategizableFactory.BuilderWithDescription  
    StrategizableFactory.BuilderWithEnabled

    StrategyFactory.FinalStep  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConfigurationEvent
    A Configuration Event.
    Constants
    Constants required for feature flags.
    StrategizableFactory
    StrategizableFactory is used to create configuration factories for Feature or FeatureGroup.
    StrategyFactory
    StrategyFactory is used to create configuration factories for SystemPropertyActivationStrategy and ServicePropertyActivationStrategy.
